==English==

===Etymology===
First attested in 1753 for the theology sense, and 1830 for the political sense. {{suffix|absolute|ism}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈæbsəluːtɪzəm/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈæb.sə.ˌlu.ˌtɪz.əm/}}
* {{audio|en-us-absolutism.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|label=political science}} The principles or practice of absolute or arbitrary government; [[despotism]].
#:* The element of ''absolutism'' and prelacy was controlling. - [[Palfrey]]
# {{context|label=theology}} Doctrine of [[preordination]]; doctrine of absolute decrees. - [[Ash]]
# The state of being absolute; the system or doctrine of the absolute or unconditional.
# Belief in a [[metaphysical]] [[absolute]].
# [[positiveness|Positiveness]].

